  "designDecisions": [
    "In-memory store (src/lib/store.ts) uses a singleton module-level object with Maps and Arrays — data persists for the lifetime of the Next.js dev server process and is pre-seeded with realistic mock data so the app is immediately usable",
    "Session auth uses a signed cookie (via the 'iron-session' pattern implemented manually with a HMAC secret baked into the code) — no environment variables needed, secret is hardcoded for zero-setup dev",
    "Password hashing uses bcryptjs (pure JS, no native binaries) for secure password storage even in the demo store",
    "Seed data (src/lib/seed.ts) auto-runs on first import of the store and populates 3 users (including 1 admin), 8 recipes across categories, sample ratings, and comments so every page renders meaningfully on first load",
    "All recipe images use curated Unsplash source URLs with fixed dimensions (no API key needed) — e.g. https://source.unsplash.com/800x600/?food,pasta — giving real visual content with zero setup",
    "Avatar images use UI Avatars API (https://ui-avatars.com) which requires no auth and generates initials-based avatars dynamically from the username",
    "Client-side state is managed with React useState/useEffect + SWR-style fetch hooks (useRecipes, useAuth) rather than a heavy state library — keeps bundle lean",
    "The in-memory store exposes typed CRUD helpers (getRecipes, createRecipe, upsertRating, etc.) that all API routes use — providing a clean separation between storage and HTTP concerns",
    "Star rating component (StarRating.tsx) supports both display-only and interactive modes with half-star visual display and full-star input for simplicity",
    "Recipe creation form (RecipeForm.tsx) handles dynamic ingredient and instruction arrays with add/remove controls, all managed with local React state and submitted as a single JSON body",
    "Filtering and search are performed in-memory on the server in /api/recipes using Array.filter() and Array.sort() — fast enough for seeded data and up to ~5000 recipes before needing a real DB",
    "Admin role is determined by a boolean flag on the User type set during seeding and registration — admin pages check the session user's isAdmin flag server-side in the API routes",
    "All UI components (Button, Input, Modal, etc.) are hand-built with Tailwind utility classes and a cn() helper — zero dependency on shadcn/ui or any component library",
    "Toast notifications (useToast hook + Toast component) use a React context with auto-dismiss timers to provide feedback for actions like saving, following, submitting ratings",
    "The app uses Next.js App Router with server components for initial page shells and client components for interactive features — pages fetch initial data server-side via direct store calls where possible to avoid client waterfalls",
    "Responsive design uses Tailwind's sm/md/lg breakpoints with a mobile-first grid: 1 column on mobile, 2 on tablet, 3 on desktop for recipe grids"
  ]
}
